<subSubSection id="69ABB7FA9B0CFFAF92AEFA8D4AE018DB" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="210EE4719B0CFFAF92AEFA8D4AE018DB" blockId="11.[151,1437,151,1514]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="13C538639B0CFFAF92AEFA8D4E4918B2" bold="true" box="[199,315,1384,1408]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B0CFFAF932AFA8D4D7D18B2" authorityName="Waichert &amp; Rodriguez &amp; Von Dohlen &amp; Pitts" authorityYear="2012" box="[323,527,1384,1408]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Auplopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="charlesi">
<emphasis id="13C538639B0CFFAF932AFA8D4D7D18B2" box="[323,527,1384,1408]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Auplopus charlesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to the Cuban species, 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B0CFFAF962AFA8D4A45184D" authority="Dreisbach." authorityName="Dreisbach." box="[1091,1335,1383,1408]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Auplopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aquilus">
<emphasis id="13C538639B0CFFAF962AFA8D4BC718B2" box="[1091,1205,1384,1408]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">A. aquilus</emphasis>
Dreisbach.
</taxonomicName>
The two species differ in coloration of the clypeus and head, which is greenish in 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B0CFFAF91A4FA6E4B321891" box="[973,1088,1419,1443]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Auplopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aquilus">
<emphasis id="13C538639B0CFFAF91A4FA6E4B321891" box="[973,1088,1419,1443]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">A. aquilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and black in 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B0CFFAF96B1FA6E4A231891" authorityName="Waichert &amp; Rodriguez &amp; Von Dohlen &amp; Pitts" authorityYear="2012" box="[1240,1361,1419,1443]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Auplopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="charlesi">
<emphasis id="13C538639B0CFFAF96B1FA6E4A231891" box="[1240,1361,1419,1443]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">A. charlesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Also, 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B0CFFAF92FEFA4B4E6218F4" authorityName="Waichert &amp; Rodriguez &amp; Von Dohlen &amp; Pitts" authorityYear="2012" box="[151,272,1454,1478]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Auplopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="charlesi">
<emphasis id="13C538639B0CFFAF92FEFA4B4E6218F4" box="[151,272,1454,1478]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">A. charlesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the hind tibia orange without purple reflections, which are present in 
<emphasis id="13C538639B0CFFAF9623FA4B4BB118F4" box="[1098,1219,1454,1478]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B0CFFAF9623FA4B4BCD18F4" box="[1098,1215,1454,1478]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Auplopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aquilus">A. aquilus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Lastly, the antenna in 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B0CFFAF92DDFA344E5718DB" box="[180,293,1489,1513]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Auplopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aquilus">
<emphasis id="13C538639B0CFFAF92DDFA344E5718DB" box="[180,293,1489,1513]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">A. aquilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has orange on the ventral surface, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B0CFFAF9167FA344CF518DB" authorityName="Waichert &amp; Rodriguez &amp; Von Dohlen &amp; Pitts" authorityYear="2012" box="[782,903,1489,1513]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Auplopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="charlesi">
<emphasis id="13C538639B0CFFAF9167FA344CF518DB" box="[782,903,1489,1513]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">A. charlesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not. The male of 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B0CFFAF96E0FA344A7018DB" authorityName="Waichert &amp; Rodriguez &amp; Von Dohlen &amp; Pitts" authorityYear="2012" box="[1161,1282,1489,1513]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Auplopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="charlesi">
<emphasis id="13C538639B0CFFAF96E0FA344A7018DB" box="[1161,1282,1489,1513]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">A. charlesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
